  "text": "High-throughput screen for KCNJ5 MUT inhibitors. KCNJ5 G151R , the most frequent mutation in APAs [CITATION_1] , was used for the primary screen. Levels of ATP in uninduced and induced cells without added test compound defined 100% and 0% effect, respectively, and served as a proxy for lethality. We screened 73,001 compounds from 19 libraries for rescue of KCNJ5",
